    "image_with_text_wKVLmh": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_CLbqn8": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Q:</strong> What’s the most rewarding part of motherhood?</p><p><strong>A:</strong> The most rewarding part of motherhood has been watching my kids grow and become their own person. As the months and years pass by you get to see how their personality changes and witness them becoming more of themselves. I get to see the behind the scenes of their lives and I love that. Being able to see a happy kid is so rewarding. </p><p><strong>Q:</strong> What do you wish someone had told you before becoming a mom?</p><p><strong>A:</strong> I feel like we have this idea that we need to have everything figured out before becoming a mom, like we need to have a house, a job, and all of these things checked off. However, most of the time you end up just figuring it out as you go. I got pregnant when I was 21 so I was really young and I still didn’t have a clue what I was doing with my life. All you need to do is take life one step at a time and figure out things as you go.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
